Ulus Jochi (Golden Horde) were more complicated and interdependent. The influence of Ulus Jochi on Moscow was especially strong in the political, economic and military spheres, while the religious field was dominated by the influence from Byzantium. The volume discusses in detail the geopolitical aspirations of Russia and the “Moscow—Third Rome” theory. In sum, the formation of the Moscow state was directly influenced by both internal and external factors, countries of the East and the West.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aDespotismzRussiaxHistory 0aDespotismzRussiaxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Russia & the Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh  aByzantium.  aGolden Horde.  aGrand Duchy of Lithuania.  aKazakh Khanate.  aKazakhstan.  aMoscow.  aMuscovy.  aRussia.  aUlus Jochi.  ageopolitics.  ahistory.  amilitary.  apower.  astate formation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074321008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781644697146zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781644697146423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781644697146/original  a978-3-11-074321-0  Academic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-074335-7  DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK